subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species resembles
B. bisetuli Yin
from Yunnan, China (
Yin, 1985
) in having
P 1 a'
on abdominal tergites I-VI, but is easily distinguished from
B. bisetuli
in the presence of foretarsal sensillum b' (absent in
B. bisetuli
), 4 anterior setae on abdominal tergite VII (only 2 in
B. bisetuli
), presence of
P 3 a
on tergites II–VI (absent in
B. bisetuli
) and 4 setae on sternite XI ( 2 setae in
B. bisetuli
).
